. ppi . . ppi

ppi pixel per inch . .

ppi .

\[ ppi = \frac{DiagPixel}{DiagLength(inch)}\] \[DiagPixel=\sqrt{HorizontalPixel^2+VerticalPixel^2}\]

idx_na=!is.na(mobile_data$dim_length) & !is.na(mobile_data$dim_breadth) & !is.na(mobile_data$year)&
  !is.na(mobile_data$px_col) & !is.na(mobile_data$px_row)

case=mobile_data[idx_na,]

case$ppi=sqrt(case$px_col^2+case$px_row^2)/case$display_size

p=ggplot(data=case , aes(x=ppi))
p+geom_histogram(binwidth = 20,fill="red",alpha=0.7)+ylab("Count")+
  xlab("PPI")+ggtitle("Histogram of PPI")

case[which.max(case$ppi),c("company","device")]
## # A tibble: 1 x 2
##   company            device
##     <chr>             <chr>
## 1    Sony Xperia XZ Premium
case %>% 
  group_by(year) %>% 
  summarise(average=mean(ppi,na.rm = T)) -> stat


p=ggplot(data=stat,aes(x=year,y=average))
p+geom_bar(stat="identity",color="black", fill="tomato")+
  ylab("Average of PPI")+
  xlab("Year")+ggtitle("PPI vs year")

mobile_data$Volume=mobile_data$dim_breadth*mobile_data$dim_length*mobile_data$dim_thickness
mobile_data$Volume=mobile_data$Volume/1000

mobile_data$density=mobile_data$weight/mobile_data$Volume

idx_water=mobile_data$density>1
mobile_data$water="Above"
mobile_data$water[idx_water]="Under"

p=ggplot(data=mobile_data,aes(x=device,y=density))
p+geom_point(aes(colour=water))+theme(axis.text.x=element_blank())+
  xlab("Device")+ylab("Density")+
  ggtitle("Finding devices denser than water")+
  geom_hline(yintercept=1)+
  scale_color_manual(values=c("blue", "red"))

idx_na=!is.na(mobile_data$price)

mobile_data[idx_na,] %>% 
  filter(company=="Samsung") %>% 
  group_by(year) %>% 
  summarise(topPrice=price[which.max(price)],topDevice=device[which.max(price)]) -> flag

p=ggplot(data=flag , aes(x=year,y=topPrice))
p+geom_bar(stat="identity",fill="orangered2",color="red",size=1)+
  xlab("Year")+ylab("Price")+ggtitle("Parchamdaran Samsung")+
  geom_text(aes(label = topDevice) ,color="blue" ,angle=90,size=3,
            fontface = "bold",position = position_stack(vjust = 0.5))

idx_na=!is.na(mobile_data$price)

mobile_data[idx_na,] %>% 
  filter(company=="Samsung") -> case
case %>% 
  group_by(year) %>% 
  summarise(topDevice=device[which.max(price)]) -> flag

case$flag="No"
idx = case$device %in% flag$topDevice
case$flag[idx]="Yes"
  

p=ggplot(data=case , aes(x=year,y=display_size,size=flag,shape=flag))
p+geom_point(colour="midnightblue")+xlab("Year")+ylab("Size")+
  theme(legend.position="none")+
  ggtitle("Price vs Year (Parchamdar is shown by triangle for each year)")
